      <lg xml:id="TolE047">
<l>tammiyal kiḷappi ṉellā veḻuttu</l>
<l>meynnilai mayakka māṉa millai</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>It is not a mistake that, when any [consonant]</l>
<l>phoneme denotes itself, it [occurs according to]</l>
<l>the disturbance in the nature of the distribution</l>
<l>of consonants.<note place="foot">E.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṭ</foreign> does never occur
          initially in standard Tamil : however, in the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṭakāram</foreign> ' the letter (or phoneme) <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṭ</foreign> ', it does occur in Anlaut.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
